{% block content %}

    <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">
        Registering to have your say about a national infrastructure project
    </h1>
    <h2 class="pins-contents-list-title govuk-heading-s">Contents</h2>
    <ol class="govuk-list pins-contents-list">
        <li><a href="#who-can-register">Who can register</a></li>
        <li><a href="#how-to-register-to-have-your-say">How to register to have your say</a></li>
        <li><a href="#find-a-project-and-register">Find a project and register</a></li>
        <li><a href="#more-detailed-advice">More detailed advice</a></li>
    </ol>

    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
        <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
            <div class="pins-step-by-step-section-main">
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="who-can-register">Who can register</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">There are several types of people and organisations who can register to have their say, including:</p>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                  <li>members of the public from the local area or anywhere in the UK</li>
                  <li>members of the public from other countries</li>
                  <li>organisations such as local authorities, councils, charities, local action groups and statutory bodies</li>
                </ul>
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="how-to-register-to-have-your-say">How to register to have your say</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">To register, you need to find the project you want to comment on and then register using the form on the project area on our website. You will need to give us your:</p>
                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                  <li>full name</li>
                  <li>address, email and telephone number</li>
                  <li>your comments about the project and how it affects you</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="govuk-body">After you register, you will be given an interested party reference. The information you give us about how the project affects you will be published on our website.</p>
                <p class="govuk-body">The developer must make the project public by advertising it and giving details about how you can register.</p>
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="find-a-project-and-register">Find a project and register</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">The registration for each project will be open for at least 28 days to give you time to register. The deadline for registering will be in the developer's advert, or you can check the project page.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body"><a href="#">Find a project and register to have your say about a national infrastructure project</a></p>
                <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="more-detailed-advice">More detailed advice</h2>
                <p class="govuk-body">If you need more detailed technical advice, you can view advice notes for each of the stages of the process.
                </p>
                <p class="govuk-body"><a href="#">Advice Note 8.2: How to register to participate in an Examination.pdf</a>
                <div class="pins-step-by-step-navigation pins-step-by-step-navigation-next">
                  <a href="/interested-party-guide/get-involved-preliminary-meetings">
